# Surface Rules & Structures (26.2)

## Surface rules (`surface_rule` in noise settings)

Still named **`surface_rule`** on 26.2 (26.3 renames to `material_rule` + registries — do not use that yet).

### `noise_threshold` condition

New optional field **`is_3d`** (default `false`). When `true`, noise is evaluated in 3D.

### Removed: `noise_gradient`

Do not author `noise_gradient` surface rules. Express the same banding with `noise_threshold` conditions (and `is_3d` if needed).

### Preliminary surface

Use condition `above_preliminary_surface` so grass/dirt layers follow `preliminary_surface_level` and do not paint cave floors. That Y comes from the noise router’s `preliminary_surface_level`, not from scanning `final_density`.

## Structure processors

### `block_rot` chaining (26.2 behavior change)

Processors now see the **block state after earlier processors**, not always the original structure block. The first processor still sees the template’s original block. Chained match-and-replace lists can stop matching once a prior processor changed the block — reorder or redesign chains accordingly.

### Flexible IDs

`protected_blocks.value` accepts a tag, ID, or list of IDs.

## Dimension types

`infiniburn` also accepts ID / list / tag. Custom dimensions need `has_ender_dragon_fight` and usually `default_clock` (e.g. `minecraft:overworld`) so time works (26.1+).
